22/02/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski signed a decree on Friday (20 February) to establish the state university in Tetovo, which would be the second state-level university in the country that teaches in Albanian. 
In a press statement on the issue, Trajkovski rejected protests by some political parties against the bill. 
He said every ethnic community in the country should have an equal right for education. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 21/02/04; MIA - 20/02/04)
